00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,980
=Episode 35=

3
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,577
The book is finished.

4
00:02:03,622 --> 00:02:04,620
And Zhanqiao's mother

5
00:02:05,755 --> 00:02:06,911
has finally found peace too.

6
00:03:25,933 --> 00:03:27,755
I'm going to say goodbye to Mrs. Lin.

7
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:46,460
You asked me

8
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:50,180
to think about going abroad with you.

9
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:53,940
Now that your mom is gone,

10
00:03:54,911 --> 00:03:56,377
I'll tell you that I'm not going.

11
00:03:59,088 --> 00:04:00,620
But don't start saying things like

12
00:04:01,180 --> 00:04:01,940
if I'm not going,

13
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,460
you won't go either.

14
00:04:05,580 --> 00:04:06,500
You're my daughter.

15
00:04:06,860 --> 00:04:08,220
I want you to be free.

16
00:04:10,460 --> 00:04:11,500
I hope you can have

17
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:12,844
the freedom I never had.

18
00:04:14,180 --> 00:04:14,620
Of course,

19
00:04:16,580 --> 00:04:18,300
you can also see it as selfishness.

20
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:21,660
Maybe I just want you

21
00:04:22,733 --> 00:04:24,288
to fulfill the dreams I never could.

22
00:04:32,140 --> 00:04:33,300
You're not young anymore.

23
00:04:37,020 --> 00:04:38,511
And we don't even live together.

24
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:44,100
I thought that if we stayed
in the same city,

25
00:04:44,740 --> 00:04:45,700
no matter what happened,

26
00:04:46,133 --> 00:04:48,360
at least we'd still be able
to look out for each other.

27
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:54,060
It's really not that big of a deal.

28
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:57,780
After seeing so many births,
deaths, and illnesses,

29
00:04:58,460 --> 00:04:59,380
life is just like this.

30
00:05:09,933 --> 00:05:11,644
Your dad and I already talked about it.

31
00:05:13,220 --> 00:05:14,020
After you go abroad,

32
00:05:14,711 --> 00:05:16,866
if anything happens to him,
he can always come to me.

33
00:05:24,660 --> 00:05:29,220
(Tofato Tea Cafe)

34
00:05:43,377 --> 00:05:44,933
When are you planning to leave?

35
00:05:55,555 --> 00:05:57,400
Originally, I planned
to leave in the summer.

36
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:02,460
I thought my mom
could hold on a little longer.

37
00:06:05,340 --> 00:06:06,380
But now that she's gone,

38
00:06:08,820 --> 00:06:09,660
I probably

39
00:06:11,380 --> 00:06:12,580
won't stay much longer either.

40
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:40,100
Before I leave,

41
00:06:42,820 --> 00:06:43,700
I should tell you

42
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:46,180
something.

43
00:06:49,740 --> 00:06:50,220
What is it?

44
00:06:54,860 --> 00:06:55,580
Your mother...

45
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:04,500
I think I may have found her.

46
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:29,780
Where is she?

47
00:07:33,860 --> 00:07:34,580
She's in Shanghai.

48
00:07:37,660 --> 00:07:39,260
I never told you before

49
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:41,940
because...

50
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:45,820
she said...

51
00:07:46,111 --> 00:07:47,800
She said I found the wrong person.

52
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:52,060
You know our family

53
00:08:56,540 --> 00:08:58,140
doesn't even have a single photo

54
00:08:58,140 --> 00:08:59,400
of the three of us together?

55
00:09:30,580 --> 00:09:31,100
What?

56
00:09:31,355 --> 00:09:32,333
You want to kill me?

57
00:09:32,777 --> 00:09:34,390
Someone like you
doesn't deserve to live.

58
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:35,180
I...

59
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:36,060
Divorce!

60
00:09:37,020 --> 00:09:38,540
I want a divorce from you!

61
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:39,460
I'm pregnant.

62
00:09:39,622 --> 00:09:41,400
You can't bring up divorce right now.

63
00:09:45,755 --> 00:09:46,777
Where's my phone?

64
00:09:48,066 --> 00:09:49,260
You took my phone, right?

65
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:50,680
You checked my phone, didn't you?

66
00:09:50,866 --> 00:09:52,066
Give me back my phone.

67
00:09:52,955 --> 00:09:53,780
I just wanted to see

68
00:09:53,780 --> 00:09:55,180
who you've been messaging every day.

69
00:09:56,244 --> 00:09:57,100
Just because of that?

70
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,140
Every night you're messaging
Xiaoxue after midnight.

71
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:01,890
I've put up with this
for a long time already!

72
00:10:01,890 --> 00:10:04,620
Everything I sent her
was work-related! It was work materials!

73
00:10:04,711 --> 00:10:05,660
Sending her those things

74
00:10:05,660 --> 00:10:07,770
is good for the company,
good for you, and good for me too.

75
00:10:07,780 --> 00:10:09,140
I didn't even send a single emoji.

76
00:10:09,755 --> 00:10:12,444
Because all these chat records
were deliberately edited by you.

77
00:10:12,780 --> 00:10:14,020
You prepared all this in advance

78
00:10:14,020 --> 00:10:14,900
just to disgust me.

79
00:10:15,460 --> 00:10:17,260
You even changed your phone password

80
00:10:17,260 --> 00:10:19,380
to my birthday
so I'd conveniently check your phone.

81
00:10:33,222 --> 00:10:34,140
Zhao Lanxin, why...

82
00:10:35,380 --> 00:10:36,340
Why can't you see

83
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:40,740
that this is my way of loving you?

84
00:10:43,380 --> 00:10:44,860
Every day, no matter where you go,

85
00:10:45,555 --> 00:10:47,088
I pick you up and drive you around.

86
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:48,822
At night, when you say you're hungry,

87
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:51,340
I get up and cook for you too.

88
00:10:53,911 --> 00:10:56,555
I'm afraid you'll fall,
so wherever you walk, I support you.

89
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:00,220
Everyone in the company knows

90
00:11:00,220 --> 00:11:01,500
that I treat you perfectly.

91
00:11:02,377 --> 00:11:04,111
If you still tell people
I treat you badly,

92
00:11:04,133 --> 00:11:05,911
then you're really just
being unreasonable.

93
00:11:06,577 --> 00:11:08,466
And most importantly, you know what?

94
00:11:10,420 --> 00:11:11,260
You have

95
00:11:12,220 --> 00:11:14,690
always been cold
and selfish with others.

96
00:11:14,690 --> 00:11:16,340
No one would ever believe your kindness.

97
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,444
Say something.

98
00:11:23,244 --> 00:11:25,955
Say something. Aren't you supposed
to have everything under control?

99
00:11:26,177 --> 00:11:27,340
Take me to the hospital.

100
00:11:27,580 --> 00:11:27,940
What?

101
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:30,220
My stomach hurts.

102
00:11:36,180 --> 00:11:38,740
(Emergency)

103
00:11:44,244 --> 00:11:45,580
What are you doing, Ling Yikai?

104
00:11:48,377 --> 00:11:50,888
The doctor told you to stay in bed more
and protect the pregnancy.

105
00:11:52,540 --> 00:11:53,460
I believe my children

106
00:11:53,460 --> 00:11:55,140
will be just as resilient as I am.

107
00:11:56,740 --> 00:11:58,733
Right. You and your children
are all resilient.

108
00:11:59,380 --> 00:12:00,340
I'm not that resilient.

109
00:12:02,022 --> 00:12:03,220
Since we can't get divorced right now,

110
00:12:03,220 --> 00:12:05,111
we'll talk about it
after the children are born.

111
00:12:05,666 --> 00:12:07,500
Starting today,
I'm sleeping in this room.

112
00:12:08,044 --> 00:12:09,580
Your lives and
the children's lives matter,

113
00:12:09,580 --> 00:12:10,866
but my life matters too.

114
00:12:11,088 --> 00:12:13,020
I need to learn how to
protect my own safety.

115
00:12:20,260 --> 00:12:21,780
I never really wanted your life.

116
00:12:36,420 --> 00:12:36,940
Zhao Lanxin,

117
00:12:38,980 --> 00:12:40,260
whether that's true or not,

118
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:42,622
I don't care, and I don't want to know.

119
00:12:42,911 --> 00:12:44,620
You can keep
playing this game by yourself.

120
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:45,866
I don't want to play anymore.

121
00:12:46,340 --> 00:12:48,220
You can keep using the company, money,

122
00:12:48,220 --> 00:12:49,860
Grandma, or the future to manipulate me.

123
00:12:50,266 --> 00:12:51,800
I don't want any of it anymore.

124
00:12:51,980 --> 00:12:53,311
As long as I can leave you,

125
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:55,820
I'm willing to pay any price.

126
00:12:59,260 --> 00:13:00,820
I thought after we had children,

127
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:02,180
you would change.

128
00:13:03,260 --> 00:13:04,420
I really did hold onto a tiny

129
00:13:04,420 --> 00:13:05,970
bit of hope
for your humanity, Ling Yikai.

130
00:13:05,980 --> 00:13:08,400
Anyone who stays with you
will eventually become like this!

131
00:13:11,755 --> 00:13:12,844
Zhao Lanxin,

132
00:13:14,555 --> 00:13:16,133
I honestly don't have the confidence

133
00:13:17,940 --> 00:13:18,980
that we can raise

134
00:13:18,980 --> 00:13:20,460
a healthy and normal child together.

135
00:13:31,420 --> 00:13:31,740
Hello?

136
00:13:32,540 --> 00:13:33,500
I brought San Mei over.

137
00:13:34,022 --> 00:13:35,580
From now on, you don't need to deal

138
00:13:35,666 --> 00:13:37,410
with San Mei and Er Jiu's
matters anymore.

139
00:13:37,580 --> 00:13:39,500
You said your place was big,

140
00:13:39,733 --> 00:13:41,577
but I didn't expect it to be this big.

141
00:13:43,620 --> 00:13:45,580
You really live alone
in such a big house, huh?

142
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:48,980
It's a bit too big.

143
00:13:51,380 --> 00:13:52,740
I booked a room next door for you.

144
00:13:53,533 --> 00:13:54,980
Move over there and stay for now.

145
00:13:55,422 --> 00:13:57,290
This place must cost
several thousand a night.

146
00:13:57,340 --> 00:13:59,010
I can't keep spending
your money staying here.

147
00:13:59,020 --> 00:13:59,660
Come on.

148
00:13:59,977 --> 00:14:02,066
There's no need to separate
things so clearly between us.

149
00:14:04,060 --> 00:14:04,780
As for Er Jiu,

150
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:08,180
if you want a divorce,

151
00:14:09,380 --> 00:14:10,500
I'll handle the rest.

152
00:14:11,533 --> 00:14:13,350
She and Er Jiu are
getting divorced by agreement.

153
00:14:13,422 --> 00:14:14,480
She's staying with me now.

154
00:14:15,088 --> 00:14:15,933
I'm marrying her.

155
00:14:18,844 --> 00:14:19,780
You're marrying her?

156
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:21,900
Are you joking?

157
00:14:22,580 --> 00:14:23,220
I'm not joking.

158
00:14:23,955 --> 00:14:25,355
Didn't expect that, did you?

159
00:14:26,133 --> 00:14:28,620
Your little act of driving
a wedge between San Mei and Er Jiu

160
00:14:28,700 --> 00:14:30,666
while pretending to be
the hero who saves the day

161
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:31,500
is over.

162
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:33,020
Zhao Lanxin,

163
00:14:33,555 --> 00:14:35,180
I never really liked you from the start.

164
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:38,460
But I believed you could
protect me from hardship.

165
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:40,460
What I didn't expect

166
00:14:41,133 --> 00:14:43,160
was that the storm itself
came from you all along.

167
00:14:44,780 --> 00:14:46,380
I'm not some morally perfect person.

168
00:14:47,260 --> 00:14:48,020
But compared to me,

169
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:49,500
you're even worse.

170
00:15:56,866 --> 00:15:57,980
Did you go look for her?

171
00:15:58,620 --> 00:15:59,380
Did you see her?

172
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:01,700
Not yet.

173
00:16:02,740 --> 00:16:03,900
So what now?

174
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,955
You're planning
to just wait there forever?

175
00:16:06,644 --> 00:16:08,980
People in clothing wholesale
usually start work quite late.

176
00:16:09,420 --> 00:16:10,340
And those doing retail

177
00:16:10,580 --> 00:16:12,260
mostly come by after work.

178
00:17:24,060 --> 00:17:28,580
(End of Season Sale.
Special Prices Storewide)

179
00:17:59,340 --> 00:18:01,140
Make way...

180
00:18:01,140 --> 00:18:01,780
Careful.

181
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:05,540
Sir,

182
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:07,555
what are you looking for?

183
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:09,620
Everything in here today

184
00:18:10,220 --> 00:18:11,860
is 20 percent off.

185
00:18:12,266 --> 00:18:13,311
Feel free to look around.

186
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:15,490
If you see something you like,
I'll give you a discount.

187
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:48,700
What did you buy? That's so much.

188
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:49,540
It's heavy.

189
00:19:49,550 --> 00:19:50,570
Wow, this is really heavy.

190
00:19:50,580 --> 00:19:52,460
Well, wholesale shopping
means buying more.

191
00:19:53,340 --> 00:19:54,060
Clothes?

192
00:19:54,444 --> 00:19:55,780
Who are you buying all this for?

193
00:19:56,044 --> 00:19:57,577
Taking them back for the neighbors.

194
00:19:57,888 --> 00:19:58,755
The key, please.

195
00:20:04,340 --> 00:20:04,820
Come on.

196
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:09,340
One, two, three.

197
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:12,020
Okay.

198
00:20:40,220 --> 00:20:42,244
The moment I saw her,
I knew it was my mom.

199
00:20:42,977 --> 00:20:44,066
It was her for sure.

200
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,111
Even though we hadn't
seen each other in decades,

201
00:20:52,140 --> 00:20:52,900
I could

202
00:20:55,260 --> 00:20:56,340
still recognize her face.

203
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:01,220
Is she doing okay?

204
00:21:02,822 --> 00:21:03,644
Pretty well.

205
00:21:07,288 --> 00:21:08,990
As long as she's doing well,
that's enough.

206
00:21:17,340 --> 00:21:18,460
If I miss her in the future,

207
00:21:20,133 --> 00:21:22,044
I'll just go buy more clothes again.

208
00:21:38,940 --> 00:21:39,620
I'll drive.

209
00:21:41,660 --> 00:21:42,060
No need.

210
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:46,500
I'm fine.

211
00:22:18,180 --> 00:22:22,420
(Lingqi Reading Platform)

212
00:22:22,420 --> 00:22:22,980
These are

213
00:22:24,580 --> 00:22:27,220
Lingqi's current
top ten bestselling titles.

214
00:22:28,540 --> 00:22:29,340
Do you know

215
00:22:29,740 --> 00:22:31,420
what their online
readership numbers are?

216
00:22:33,155 --> 00:22:35,060
Every single one
has over a million readers.

217
00:22:35,540 --> 00:22:38,420
Lingqi's average daily active users
have already hit

218
00:22:38,577 --> 00:22:39,866
one hundred million.

219
00:22:40,420 --> 00:22:42,180
And now, let's look

220
00:22:42,340 --> 00:22:44,860
at our user data
and the situation with our authors.

221
00:22:46,044 --> 00:22:47,420
Wenliu, you tell everyone.

222
00:22:47,660 --> 00:22:48,860
I'm afraid I'll die

223
00:22:48,977 --> 00:22:50,200
from anger halfway through.

224
00:22:50,300 --> 00:22:51,420
At the moment,

225
00:22:51,540 --> 00:22:53,580
about one-third of our authors

226
00:22:54,060 --> 00:22:54,980
have already

227
00:22:55,340 --> 00:22:57,580
been privately approached by Lingqi.

228
00:22:57,940 --> 00:22:58,820
For SS-tier authors,

229
00:22:58,940 --> 00:23:00,460
their minimum guarantee is over 200,

230
00:23:00,577 --> 00:23:03,311
plus backend profit sharing
on top of the 3,000 base guarantee.

231
00:23:03,580 --> 00:23:05,660
They only want SS-tier
and S-tier star authors.

232
00:23:05,822 --> 00:23:06,680
What about the rest?

233
00:23:06,733 --> 00:23:07,577
They don't want them.

234
00:23:07,580 --> 00:23:08,380
What do you mean?

235
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:10,060
It means they look down on them.

236
00:23:10,220 --> 00:23:11,600
They only want the very best.

237
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:14,260
Mr. Fan,

238
00:23:14,355 --> 00:23:16,200
Ms. Zhao is waiting
for you in the office.

239
00:23:22,540 --> 00:23:23,060
Mr. Fan.

240
00:23:24,244 --> 00:23:26,311
I have been hearing
bad news all this morning,

241
00:23:26,444 --> 00:23:27,620
and judging from your face,

242
00:23:27,666 --> 00:23:29,800
I don't think
you're bringing good news either.

243
00:23:30,460 --> 00:23:30,900
Go ahead.

244
00:23:31,577 --> 00:23:33,577
How did Lingqi Platform
disgust you this time?

245
00:23:34,111 --> 00:23:35,060
Gu Yan wants to leave.

246
00:23:36,133 --> 00:23:37,177
It's Lingqi Platform.

247
00:23:38,780 --> 00:23:41,220
You know how our writing model works.

248
00:23:41,460 --> 00:23:41,860
Yeah.

249
00:23:42,422 --> 00:23:43,688
AI collaborative writing, right?

250
00:23:43,755 --> 00:23:45,420
Can you accept big data-driven creation?

251
00:23:47,355 --> 00:23:48,540
As long as you can keep me

252
00:23:48,540 --> 00:23:49,860
where I am now,

253
00:23:50,577 --> 00:23:51,860
there's nothing I can't accept.

254
00:23:53,580 --> 00:23:54,700
Did Dai Shan approach him?

255
00:23:54,860 --> 00:23:55,780
Are they still talking,

256
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:57,420
or has he already decided?

257
00:23:58,460 --> 00:24:00,460
Didn't you say you
had Gu Yan under control?

258
00:24:02,300 --> 00:24:03,540
I'm worried he'll leave.

259
00:24:04,022 --> 00:24:06,333
I'm worried Dai Shan
promised him something bigger.

260
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:08,340
AI co-writing is the trend now.

261
00:24:08,533 --> 00:24:09,990
From the way things are developing...

262
00:24:10,020 --> 00:24:11,660
Don't give me that.

263
00:24:11,940 --> 00:24:13,820
Do you think I don't know who Gu Yan is?

264
00:24:14,300 --> 00:24:15,740
Prospects?

265
00:24:15,900 --> 00:24:16,900
Trends?

266
00:24:17,220 --> 00:24:18,980
If he really thought
about things that way,

267
00:24:19,460 --> 00:24:21,220
would he have left
Lin Zhanqiao back then

268
00:24:21,220 --> 00:24:22,555
and signed with you instead?

269
00:24:24,420 --> 00:24:25,500
All along the way,

270
00:24:25,980 --> 00:24:26,900
people have said

271
00:24:27,511 --> 00:24:29,155
that I relied on Lin Zhanqiao,

272
00:24:29,177 --> 00:24:29,900
(Gu Yan)

273
00:24:29,900 --> 00:24:30,860
copied He Han,

274
00:24:31,540 --> 00:24:33,100
and rode on Phantom Knight's fame.

275
00:24:34,340 --> 00:24:35,100
But so what?

276
00:24:36,488 --> 00:24:39,355
Aren't I still the most valuable
online fiction author right now?

277
00:24:41,860 --> 00:24:43,100
So, relying on AI

278
00:24:45,740 --> 00:24:47,340
isn't anything special to me.

279
00:24:48,660 --> 00:24:49,260
Smooth.

280
00:24:49,780 --> 00:24:50,420
Clear-headed.

281
00:24:50,740 --> 00:24:51,580
So that's why

282
00:24:51,580 --> 00:24:53,660
you made it this far?

283
00:24:54,088 --> 00:24:55,377
No need to compliment me.

284
00:24:56,755 --> 00:24:58,620
I know all of you
actually look down on me.

285
00:25:01,020 --> 00:25:01,860
But that's fine.

286
00:25:05,066 --> 00:25:07,488
It lets me negotiate with
you without any burden.

287
00:25:10,060 --> 00:25:11,900
Let's hear what
conditions you still have.

288
00:25:16,380 --> 00:25:16,860
First,

289
00:25:18,180 --> 00:25:19,140
a five-million advance.

290
00:25:19,777 --> 00:25:20,911
Pay me within three days.

291
00:25:21,740 --> 00:25:22,060
Second,

292
00:25:22,740 --> 00:25:23,460
I want your car.

293
00:25:24,100 --> 00:25:24,820
The Lotus?

294
00:25:25,140 --> 00:25:25,420
Yes.

295
00:25:27,460 --> 00:25:28,020
Why?

296
00:25:29,620 --> 00:25:31,500
He Han used to have not only this suite,

297
00:25:33,060 --> 00:25:33,860
but that car too.

298
00:25:37,260 --> 00:25:39,580
Well, I also need to see
your contract with Zhao Lanxin.

299
00:25:40,180 --> 00:25:42,300
My contract with Zhao Lanxin
is based on word count.

300
00:25:43,222 --> 00:25:44,733
I still owe 500,000 words.

301
00:25:45,620 --> 00:25:47,060
Including the drafts I already have,

302
00:25:48,444 --> 00:25:49,844
I can finish it in a week.

303
00:25:54,060 --> 00:25:56,100
I remember when I first came to you,

304
00:25:56,100 --> 00:25:59,100
you weren't particularly
interested in Lingqi.

305
00:25:59,100 --> 00:26:00,380
What exactly

306
00:26:00,380 --> 00:26:01,980
made you change your mind?

307
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:03,555
You said it yourself.

308
00:26:04,340 --> 00:26:05,580
A wise man knows when to adapt.

309
00:26:06,620 --> 00:26:07,180
What else?

310
00:26:07,580 --> 00:26:08,380
And Zhao Lanxin

311
00:26:08,380 --> 00:26:10,100
isn't worth standing with.

312
00:26:10,300 --> 00:26:11,620
What if it were Lin Zhanqiao?

313
00:26:15,688 --> 00:26:18,044
She might actually be able
to put up a fight against you.

314
00:26:20,220 --> 00:26:21,100
That's what you want.

315
00:26:21,700 --> 00:26:22,020
Here.

316
00:26:23,180 --> 00:26:24,020
Take a look at this.

317
00:26:24,660 --> 00:26:26,260
This is the future positioning

318
00:26:26,260 --> 00:26:27,780
for your writing and personal brand.

319
00:26:27,844 --> 00:26:29,377
As long as you follow it step by step,

320
00:26:29,422 --> 00:26:30,900
you'll surpass your current peak.

321
00:26:31,340 --> 00:26:32,580
(Analysis of Similar Works)

322
00:26:32,580 --> 00:26:33,820
(Shattered Six States,
Fantasy/Eastern Fantasy, by He Han)

323
00:26:34,244 --> 00:26:35,466
Using He Han as the benchmark?

324
00:26:36,860 --> 00:26:38,860
Surpass He Han completely.

325
00:26:39,180 --> 00:26:40,940
Surpassing him isn't difficult at all.

326
00:26:41,660 --> 00:26:43,060
Haven't I already surpassed him?

327
00:26:44,500 --> 00:26:46,540
I've never taken He Han seriously.

328
00:26:47,500 --> 00:26:48,580
Neither have my readers.

329
00:26:49,488 --> 00:26:51,260
He's nothing more
than a comparison target.

330
00:26:52,620 --> 00:26:53,820
But He Han

331
00:26:54,660 --> 00:26:56,380
was already at his peak.

332
00:26:56,660 --> 00:26:58,260
The real peak was not him

333
00:26:59,100 --> 00:27:00,100
but Phantom Knight.

334
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:06,420
I want the publicity plan revised.

335
00:27:06,866 --> 00:27:08,333
Use Phantom Knight as the benchmark.

336
00:27:08,740 --> 00:27:10,020
If Phantom Knight

337
00:27:10,020 --> 00:27:11,500
created the Online Fiction 1.0 era,

338
00:27:12,100 --> 00:27:13,020
then starting from me,

339
00:27:13,580 --> 00:27:14,620
this will be the 2.0 era.

340
00:27:15,777 --> 00:27:17,400
There's no need for He Han's name.

341
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:31,244
Didn't expect
that the car would be so popular, huh?

342
00:27:34,155 --> 00:27:36,088
I've already finalized
the deal with Dai Shan.

343
00:27:37,733 --> 00:27:39,533
I never liked Zhao Lanxin to begin with.

344
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:42,200
Dai Shan offered me
a better opportunity,

345
00:27:42,380 --> 00:27:42,860
so I left.

346
00:27:43,488 --> 00:27:45,488
You don't need to
explain any of this to me.

347
00:27:47,088 --> 00:27:49,020
Whether you work with
Zhao Lanxin or Dai Shan,

348
00:27:49,780 --> 00:27:50,780
I honestly don't care.

349
00:27:53,340 --> 00:27:54,460
Even now,

350
00:27:56,020 --> 00:27:57,260
aside from San Mei and Er Jiu,

351
00:27:58,466 --> 00:28:00,288
you're still the only person I trust.

352
00:28:02,340 --> 00:28:03,060
Only you

353
00:28:03,060 --> 00:28:04,660
treated me like an equal partner.

354
00:28:05,540 --> 00:28:07,020
You cared about my future well-being.

355
00:28:08,380 --> 00:28:09,740
Zhao Lanxin and Dai Shan never did.

356
00:28:11,540 --> 00:28:12,940
To them, I was just a tool.

357
00:28:13,333 --> 00:28:15,990
All they wanted was to squeeze
my value out as quickly as possible.

358
00:28:16,177 --> 00:28:18,022
They don't care what kind of problems

359
00:28:19,060 --> 00:28:20,940
I'll face a year from now,

360
00:28:20,940 --> 00:28:22,488
let alone three or five years later.

361
00:28:23,140 --> 00:28:23,740
All they need

362
00:28:23,740 --> 00:28:24,980
is to find the next Gu Yan.

363
00:28:26,100 --> 00:28:26,780
So what?

364
00:28:29,700 --> 00:28:31,340
What you wanted was never equality

365
00:28:32,100 --> 00:28:33,380
or healthy long-term growth.

366
00:28:34,100 --> 00:28:35,060
I wanted to feel valued.

367
00:28:35,311 --> 00:28:37,222
I wanted to be treated like I mattered.

368
00:28:37,444 --> 00:28:39,140
I wanted someone around me at all times,

369
00:28:39,540 --> 00:28:40,140
praising me.

370
00:28:41,020 --> 00:28:42,660
Even if I knew all of it was fake,

371
00:28:43,180 --> 00:28:44,060
all calculated,

372
00:28:44,244 --> 00:28:46,488
and all just people using me,
I still wanted it.

373
00:28:47,060 --> 00:28:48,300
If you could treat me that way,

374
00:28:49,340 --> 00:28:50,780
I would've never gone to Zhao Lanxin.

375
00:28:51,740 --> 00:28:53,620
I would've kept trying
to maintain my value

376
00:28:54,180 --> 00:28:55,380
just to keep you by my side.

377
00:28:55,740 --> 00:28:56,380
I can't do that.

378
00:28:57,580 --> 00:28:58,700
I can't do that for anyone.

379
00:29:00,860 --> 00:29:02,740
I can lose everything. I can fail.

380
00:29:04,020 --> 00:29:04,780
But I can never

381
00:29:04,780 --> 00:29:06,460
betray my own judgment and feelings.

382
00:29:08,020 --> 00:29:08,620
I know.

383
00:29:09,866 --> 00:29:11,377
That's why I came here

384
00:29:11,860 --> 00:29:12,820
to say goodbye.

385
00:29:14,044 --> 00:29:15,333
I heard you're going abroad.

386
00:29:16,220 --> 00:29:17,933
I never planned to convince you to stay.

387
00:29:19,460 --> 00:29:21,220
Even though I resent you
for not keeping me,

388
00:29:21,933 --> 00:29:22,911
I still respect you.

389
00:29:23,900 --> 00:29:25,740
Zhao Lanxin and Dai Shan went all out

390
00:29:25,740 --> 00:29:27,311
to give me everything I wanted.

391
00:29:27,866 --> 00:29:29,355
But I still look down on them.

392
00:29:30,155 --> 00:29:32,140
How much we've gained
and how much we've lost

393
00:29:32,866 --> 00:29:34,860
isn't something
we should settle right now.

394
00:29:35,888 --> 00:29:37,555
But that day
won't stay far away forever.

395
00:29:39,466 --> 00:29:41,060
Whether this trade was worth it or not,

396
00:29:41,860 --> 00:29:43,260
if we ever meet again in the future,

397
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:45,200
we can talk about it then.

398
00:29:46,266 --> 00:29:47,555
There's one more thing.

399
00:29:51,220 --> 00:29:52,900
Whether you're Phantom Knight or not,

400
00:29:54,260 --> 00:29:54,980
this time,

401
00:29:55,980 --> 00:29:57,900
I'm going to crush
that name beneath my feet.

402
00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:00,860
I'm the one standing at the top now.

403
00:30:07,820 --> 00:30:09,340
The dullest thing

404
00:30:10,577 --> 00:30:12,600
about a game built on winning and losing

405
00:30:13,660 --> 00:30:14,420
is when your rival

406
00:30:15,260 --> 00:30:16,580
doesn't even want to play.

407
00:30:35,660 --> 00:30:36,180
Mr. Fan.

408
00:30:36,355 --> 00:30:37,422
He replied to you?

409
00:30:41,380 --> 00:30:44,200
(Lingqi Reading. Gu Yan continues
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui)

410
00:30:44,311 --> 00:30:46,660
(How did the sequel
surpass the original work?)

411
00:30:55,620 --> 00:30:57,100
Dai Shan has already signed Gu Yan.

412
00:31:11,733 --> 00:31:13,311
I just came back from Lingqi Platform.

413
00:31:13,688 --> 00:31:14,780
What were you doing there?

414
00:31:15,460 --> 00:31:17,140
Curious. Wanted to see
things for myself.

415
00:31:17,200 --> 00:31:19,066
Know your enemy
and know yourself, you know?

416
00:31:19,300 --> 00:31:20,220
So, what did you learn?

417
00:31:21,060 --> 00:31:21,660
Lingqi Platform

418
00:31:21,660 --> 00:31:23,100
is going to give Gu Yan's
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui

419
00:31:23,100 --> 00:31:23,930
a big promotional push.

420
00:31:23,940 --> 00:31:25,820
They're going all out,
building hype around it.

421
00:31:26,977 --> 00:31:28,460
So Gu Yan signed with them too?

422
00:31:29,060 --> 00:31:30,140
And their marketing strategy

423
00:31:30,140 --> 00:31:32,180
directly targets Phantom Knight.

424
00:31:32,311 --> 00:31:34,644
They want to shape Gu Yan
into No. 1 in online fiction.

425
00:31:34,780 --> 00:31:35,940
Because Dai Shan knows

426
00:31:35,940 --> 00:31:37,644
Gu Yan loves this kind of attention.

427
00:31:38,780 --> 00:31:40,740
I wonder if Phantom Knight would be

428
00:31:40,740 --> 00:31:42,066
furious seeing articles like this.

429
00:31:42,133 --> 00:31:44,610
The original author worked so hard
to build the novel's foundation,

430
00:31:44,620 --> 00:31:46,444
yet Gu Yan gained fame
just by continuing it.

431
00:31:46,533 --> 00:31:49,190
Not only is he ungrateful instead
of respecting the original author,

432
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:51,590
but he's now also stepping on their name
to promote himself.

433
00:31:52,420 --> 00:31:53,100
Don't worry.

434
00:31:53,860 --> 00:31:55,860
Phantom Knight would never
take a clown like that

435
00:31:55,860 --> 00:31:56,620
seriously.

436
00:32:05,340 --> 00:32:06,511
Can't take it anymore?

437
00:32:07,220 --> 00:32:08,460
We came from the same roots.

438
00:32:08,860 --> 00:32:10,500
Why destroy each other like this?

439
00:32:11,540 --> 00:32:12,340
Beg me.

440
00:32:13,460 --> 00:32:13,860
Please,

441
00:32:14,300 --> 00:32:15,220
I'm begging you.

442
00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:15,980
Please.

443
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:18,400
Of course,

444
00:32:18,900 --> 00:32:19,940
it's also about giving

445
00:32:20,020 --> 00:32:22,140
those outstanding writers

446
00:32:22,140 --> 00:32:23,580
who are still diligently typing away

447
00:32:24,620 --> 00:32:25,540
a way to make a living.

448
00:32:44,066 --> 00:32:45,711
Back then, you were just like me.

449
00:32:46,780 --> 00:32:47,300
We...

450
00:32:49,180 --> 00:32:51,100
We all walked this road together.

451
00:32:52,580 --> 00:32:53,700
At the beginning,

452
00:32:53,866 --> 00:32:55,466
hardly anyone chose this path.

453
00:32:57,088 --> 00:32:58,460
And now, after all this effort,

454
00:32:59,580 --> 00:33:00,340
it's finally become

455
00:33:00,820 --> 00:33:02,020
a real industry.

456
00:33:02,660 --> 00:33:03,020
Right?

457
00:33:05,860 --> 00:33:06,660
I don't believe it.

458
00:33:07,740 --> 00:33:08,580
I don't believe

459
00:33:09,380 --> 00:33:11,780
you can really bear
to watch a large-scale purge

460
00:33:12,044 --> 00:33:14,300
where low-quality
content drives out the good work.

461
00:33:15,533 --> 00:33:16,800
I don't believe it.

462
00:33:19,660 --> 00:33:20,420
But Fan,

463
00:33:21,380 --> 00:33:23,660
expansion is always
rough in the beginning.

464
00:33:24,660 --> 00:33:26,140
AI co-writing is the same.

465
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:31,060
I know where the problems are right now.

466
00:33:31,500 --> 00:33:34,620
But my top priority is grabbing
users and market share.

467
00:33:35,060 --> 00:33:36,260
It's about scale.

468
00:33:36,577 --> 00:33:38,100
The low-quality content is temporary.

469
00:33:38,100 --> 00:33:41,500
Once things stabilize gradually,
we'll still move toward premium content.

470
00:33:41,780 --> 00:33:43,420
I'm afraid these talented authors

471
00:33:43,420 --> 00:33:44,660
won't have the patience

472
00:33:44,660 --> 00:33:46,210
to wait until that day comes.

473
00:33:46,210 --> 00:33:48,488
There will be another generation
of talented authors.

474
00:33:59,060 --> 00:34:00,620
This generation's top authors

475
00:34:00,620 --> 00:34:01,860
may not necessarily

476
00:34:01,860 --> 00:34:04,900
remain at the top once
AI collaboration fully takes over.

477
00:34:05,260 --> 00:34:07,420
Their thinking is too rigid.

478
00:34:07,420 --> 00:34:08,980
They can't let go of themselves.

479
00:34:09,340 --> 00:34:11,700
The things they write
aren't as effective

480
00:34:11,777 --> 00:34:13,355
as what the newer writers produce.

481
00:34:13,740 --> 00:34:15,300
So why sign them at all?

482
00:34:16,060 --> 00:34:17,780
Why waste their time?

483
00:34:18,100 --> 00:34:19,980
To make room

484
00:34:20,900 --> 00:34:21,980
for my new writers to rise.

485
00:34:25,020 --> 00:34:26,700
So you'd rather sacrifice them.

486
00:34:29,511 --> 00:34:30,777
That's the real reason

487
00:34:31,300 --> 00:34:32,940
you paid to sign them,

488
00:34:34,020 --> 00:34:34,380
isn't it?

489
00:34:38,860 --> 00:34:39,660
Walk me out?

490
00:34:40,340 --> 00:34:40,820
Sorry.

491
00:34:41,200 --> 00:34:42,555
We're not heading the same way.

492
00:34:42,620 --> 00:34:43,790
Let's go our separate ways.

493
00:34:51,977 --> 00:34:54,200
(Once I finish continuing
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui,)

494
00:34:54,210 --> 00:34:56,577
(that will also mark
my final farewell to Phantom Knight.)

495
00:34:57,020 --> 00:34:57,900
(And I must admit,)

496
00:34:57,933 --> 00:34:59,000
(the Online Fiction 1.0 era)

497
00:34:59,088 --> 00:35:01,340
(represented by Phantom Knight
has already come to an end.)

498
00:35:01,622 --> 00:35:02,533
(I also acknowledge)

499
00:35:02,820 --> 00:35:04,340
(that AI technology is progressing,)

500
00:35:04,820 --> 00:35:06,380
(a gift this era has given to writers.)

501
00:35:07,100 --> 00:35:08,340
(Lingqi's AI co-writing)

502
00:35:08,420 --> 00:35:10,620
(has brought me entirely
new excitement and challenges.)

503
00:35:11,340 --> 00:35:13,420
(AI co-writing
combines technology and innovation,)

504
00:35:13,666 --> 00:35:16,222
(while pushing beyond the boundaries
of traditional storytelling.)

505
00:35:16,866 --> 00:35:18,500
(I'm not someone
who clings to old ways.)

506
00:35:18,777 --> 00:35:19,900
(I'm willing to embrace)

507
00:35:19,900 --> 00:35:21,240
(everything this era has brought.)

508
00:35:21,422 --> 00:35:22,460
(Using AI-assisted writing,)

509
00:35:22,780 --> 00:35:24,460
(I will create
the Online Fiction 2.0 era)

510
00:35:24,460 --> 00:35:25,580
(represented by me, Gu Yan.)

511
00:35:33,540 --> 00:35:35,060
The dullest thing

512
00:35:36,377 --> 00:35:38,422
about a game built on winning and losing

513
00:35:39,380 --> 00:35:40,100
is when your rival

514
00:35:40,980 --> 00:35:42,300
doesn't even want to play.

515
00:35:56,580 --> 00:36:01,980
(A small country threatened by war...)

516
00:36:12,340 --> 00:36:13,060
Are you asleep?

517
00:36:17,820 --> 00:36:18,340
What's wrong?

518
00:36:20,180 --> 00:36:21,420
If you're still awake,

519
00:36:23,044 --> 00:36:24,155
let's talk for a bit.

520
00:36:27,580 --> 00:36:28,300
Er Jiu agreed.

521
00:36:28,977 --> 00:36:29,940
He'll take the money,

522
00:36:30,066 --> 00:36:32,466
sign the divorce papers with you,
and leave Shanghai.

523
00:36:38,980 --> 00:36:39,700
You know this.

524
00:36:40,022 --> 00:36:41,620
Domestic violence can't be forgiven.

525
00:36:45,511 --> 00:36:47,333
I never said I was going to forgive him.

526
00:36:49,660 --> 00:36:50,340
What did he say?

527
00:36:53,820 --> 00:36:55,340
(Temporarily Closed)

528
00:37:14,844 --> 00:37:16,866
This is all I can give you right now.

529
00:37:17,377 --> 00:37:18,688
If you think it's not enough,

530
00:37:18,777 --> 00:37:19,888
I'll figure out another way.

531
00:37:19,933 --> 00:37:22,100
(5,000,000 yuan)

532
00:37:22,620 --> 00:37:23,460
So much money?

533
00:37:25,340 --> 00:37:26,980
I couldn't make that in 10 or 20 years.

534
00:37:29,460 --> 00:37:30,460
I was just thinking,

535
00:37:32,222 --> 00:37:34,333
why should I take
this much money from you?

536
00:37:35,060 --> 00:37:35,740
I owe you.

537
00:37:37,540 --> 00:37:38,980
We once swore

538
00:37:39,288 --> 00:37:40,740
to share blessings and hardships.

539
00:37:41,100 --> 00:37:41,980
You don't owe me.

540
00:37:44,288 --> 00:37:45,300
If anyone owes someone,

541
00:37:46,060 --> 00:37:47,140
it's me who owes San Mei.

542
00:37:49,900 --> 00:37:50,740
I loved her,

543
00:37:52,380 --> 00:37:53,180
but I also hurt her.

544
00:37:56,540 --> 00:37:58,380
When I married her, I already knew

545
00:38:01,288 --> 00:38:02,888
her heart only had room for you.

546
00:38:05,780 --> 00:38:07,100
I thought I could accept that.

547
00:38:08,740 --> 00:38:10,220
But after we got married, I realized

548
00:38:14,060 --> 00:38:14,700
it was too hard.

549
00:38:21,180 --> 00:38:22,500
At one point I even thought,

550
00:38:22,755 --> 00:38:23,977
